# Lab: File path traversal, simple case

## Vulnerability Type
Broken Access Control

## Difficulty
apprentice

## Platform
PortSwigger Web Security Academy

## Goal
To solve the lab, retrieve the contents of the /etc/passwd file.

## Root Cause
This lab contains a path traversal vulnerability in the display of product images. The application does not properly validate user-controlled file paths.

## Exploitation Steps
1. Browse the application and select any product  
2. intercept the request in Burp Suite  
3. identify parameter that fetches image from server, for example:
```text
image=abc.png
